The paper proposes a mixture model for clustering of high dimensional binary data, which is a common problem in machine learning and data mining. The paper also emphasizes the efficiency of the proposed algorithm, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of probability distributions and optimization algorithms, which are common topics in the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DM (Data Mining). The paper also mentions the application of the proposed algorithm to text data, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) or cs.CV (Computer Vision) depending on the type of text data used. Overall, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DM, cs.CL, and cs.CV.
